description: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 2.

name: cutaneous Leishmaniasis
description: Leishmaniasis affecting the skin. It is the most common form of leishmaniasis. It presents with erythematous macules and papules, and nodules which may eventually ulcerate. The lesions appear in the bite site in the exposed skin areas.

name: cutaneous Leishmaniasis
description: Is a parasitic infection of  the skin caused by the Leishmania protozoan parasite

name: embryonic stage 4
description: Nuclear division 10-13. Polar buds divide twice and become tightly grouped at the posterior pole by the end of this stage. Nuclei visible at the rim of the embryo. Stage 4 ends with the beginning of cellularization. Duration at 25 degrees C: approx. 50 minutes (80-130 minutes after egg laying).

name: CBA/CaJ
description: CBA/CaJ is a mouse strain as described in Jackson Laboratory http://jaxmice.jax.org/strain/000654.html

name: obsolete_Legg-Calve-Perthes Disease
description: An osteochondrosis that results_in death and fracture located_in hip joint.

name: ZHBTc4-mESC
description: ZHBTc4 undifferentiated mouse embryonic stem cells originated from a male mouse of the 129/Ola strain, and received as frozen ampoules from D. Levasseur (University of Iowa). These cells lack functional endogenous Oct4 alleles and harbor a regulatable Oct4 transgene.

name: Paranasal Sinus Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma
description: A rare adenoid cystic carcinoma that arises from the paranasal sinuses. It usually has an aggressive clinical course characterized by high recurrence rates and distant metastases.

name: Rectal Tubulovillous Adenoma
description: A neoplasm that arises from the glandular epithelium of the rectal mucosa. It is characterized by tubular and villous architectural patterns. The neoplastic glandular cells have dysplastic features.

name: transposition
description: A genetic modification introduced into an individual as the result of transposase activity

name: precuneus cortex volume measurement
description: Quantification of the volume of the precuneus cortex.

name: anterior endoderm anlage in statu nascendi
chloride measurement
description: A quantitative measurement of the amount of chloride present in a sample.

name: facial depth measurement
description: quantification of some aspect of facial depth, such as the distance from the tip of the nose to the tip of the ear lobe

name: white matter growth measurement
description: Quantification of any aspect of growth of the white matter during development

name: traffic air pollution measurement
description: quantification of some aspect of air pollution through traffic, such as annual average NO2 exposure estimates derived using land use regression modeling

name: neonatal systemic lupus erythematosus
description: A self-limited skin rash that appears in the neonatal period and usually resolves in four to six months after birth. It is caused by placental transfer of maternal autoantibodies, usually anti-Ro antibody. In a minority of cases, it is associated with congenital heart block, hepatitis, or thrombocytopenia. The mothers of the affected babies may be asymptomatic or suffer from systemic lupus erythematosus, Sjogren's syndrome, or rheumatoid arthritis.

name: Aeromonas hydrophila infection
description: Aeromonas hydrophila infection is a bacterial disease caused by infection from the Aeromonas hydrophila bacteria.

name: coffee consumption measurement
description: the quantification of some coffee consumption or coffee consumption-related behaviour, usually self-reported via a questionnaire

name: tauopathy
description: Neurodegenerative disorders involving deposition of abnormal tau protein isoforms (tau proteins) in neurons and glial cells in the brain. Pathological aggregations of tau proteins are associated with mutation of the tau gene on chromosome 17 in patients with alzheimer disease; dementia; parkinsonian disorders; progressive supranuclear palsy (supranuclear palsy, progressive); and corticobasal degeneration.

name: tauopathy
description: Tauopathies are heterogeneous neurodegenerative diseases characterized by the deposition of abnormal tau protein in the brain.

name: obsolete_eye structure
description: A cavitated compound organ that transduces light waves into neural signals.

name: obsolete_eye structure
description: An organ of sight; especially: a nearly spherical hollow organ that is lined with a sensitive retina, is lodged in a bony orbit in the skull, is the vertebrate organ of sight, and is normally paired.n2: All the visible structures within and surrounding the orbit and including eyelids, eyelashes, and eyebrows.

name: obsolete_eye structure
description: A light-perceptive organ consisting of an aggregation of optic elements (ommatidia) generally located on each side of the head; the cuticular part (cornea) consists of several hundred circular corneal facets (lenses); bounded by the ocular sclerite.

name: obsolete_eye structure
description: An organ of sight; especially: a nearly spherical hollow organ that is lined with a sensitive retina, is lodged in a bony orbit in the skull, is the vertebrate organ of sight, and is normally paired.

name: obsolete_eye structure
description: The compound eye is a light sensing organ composed of ommatidia.

name: obsolete_eye structure
description: Cavitated compound organ that consists of the neural retina, lens, cornea and iris and is the sensory apparatus of the visual system.

name: disposition index measurement
description: quantification of the disposition index, the product of measures of insulin sensitivity and firstphase insulin secretion, shown to predict conversion to diabetes

name: Monieziasis
description: Infection of ruminants with tapeworms of the genus Moniezia.

name: tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member EDAR measurement
description: quantification of the amount of tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member EDAR in a sample

name: leaf component
description: A leaf component is a plant component which is part of a leaf.

name: Shaken Baby Syndrome
description: Brain injuries resulted from vigorous shaking of an infant or young child held by the chest, shoulders, or extremities causing extreme cranial acceleration. It is characterized by the intracranial and intraocular hemorrhages with no evident external trauma. Serious cases may result in death.

name: 1,5 anhydroglucitol measurement
description: quantification of the amount of 1,5 anydroglucitol in a sample

name: icSHAPE
description: In vivo click selective 2’-hydroxyl acylation and profiling experiment (icSHAPE)

name: NET-Seq
description: Native elongating transcript sequencing (NET-Seq)

name: elongating embryo Ce
description: C. elegans 350-620min after first cleavage at 20 Centigrade. Cell number remains at ~560 cells, with some new cells generated and some cells go through programmed cell death. The stage that embryo starts elongation till elongation is over.

name: ELR
description: Transformed BJ cells expressing hTERT, SV40 early region and RAS.

name: Chlamydophila infectious disease
description: Infections with bacteria of the genus chlamydophila.

name: Chlamydophila infectious disease
description: Infections with bacteria of the genus CHLAMYDOPHILA.

name: lycopene measurement
description: quantification in a sample (eg blood) of lycopene, a bright red carotene and carotenoid pigment and phytochemical found in tomatoes and other red fruits and vegetables, such as red carrots, watermelons and papayas

name: outbred
description: Propety of an organism which indicates that the organism's parents are not closely related (e.g. family members).

name: test result
description: The recorded value of the outcome of some test.

name: thiopurine metabolite measurement
description: Quantification of the metabolites of thiopurine compounds.

name: CB306
description: Strain of C. elegans Levamisole resistant, recessive, Kinky Unc.

name: surgical resection
description: Surgical removal of all or part of an organ, tissue, or structure.

name: minor histocompatibility congenic strain
description: A congenic strain in which the donor allele transferred to the host strain background is a minor histocompatibility gene.

name: COLO 680N
description: Human squamous cell carcinoma cell line (DSMZ catalog number ACC 182)

name: HCC1263
description: Human colorectal adenocarcinoma cell line from 20-year-old Black female

name: Commotio Cordis
description: A sudden CARDIAC ARRHYTHMIA (e.g., VENTRICULAR FIBRILLATION) caused by a blunt, non-penetrating impact to the precordial region of chest wall. Commotio cordis often results in sudden death without prompt cardiopulmonary defibrillation.

name: Psoas abscess
description: Abscess of the PSOAS MUSCLES resulting usually from disease of the lumbar vertebrae, with the pus descending into the muscle sheath. The infection is most commonly tuberculous or staphylococcal.

name: adrenocortical adenoma
description: A benign neoplasm that can arise from any of the adrenal cortical layers. It can be associated with the overproduction of glucocorticoids (Cushing's syndrome), androgenic or estrogenic steroids (adrenogenital syndrome), or mineralocorticoids (Conn's syndrome). (Sternberg Diagnostic Surgical Pathology, 3rd ed.)

name: adrenocortical adenoma
description: Adrenocortical adenomas are benign tumors of the adrenal cortex.

name: monoclonal B-cell lymphocytosis
description: A monoclonal expansion of B-lymphocytes with or without the characteristic immunophenotype of chronic lymphocytic leukemia.

name: infant cerebrospinal fluid volume measurement
description: quantification of the volume of cerebrospinal fluid in an infant's brain

name: susceptibility to rubella infection measurement
description: Quantification of an individual's susceptibility to shingles

name: psoriatic arthritis
description: Joint inflammation associated with psoriasis.

name: psoriatic arthritis
description: A type of inflammatory arthritis associated with PSORIASIS, often involving the axial joints and the peripheral terminal interphalangeal joints. It is characterized by the presence of HLA-B27-associated SPONDYLARTHROPATHY, and the absence of rheumatoid factor.

name: obsolete_floor plate rhombomere 5
description: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 5.

name: erythrocyte measurement
description: Is a quantification of some aspect of erythrocyte function, quantity, or composition.

name: embryonic stage 5
description: Cellularization. Stage 5 begins when cellularization starts. Near the end of this stage the pole cells begin to migrate dorsally and ventral midline cells acquire an irregular, wavy appearance. Stage 5 ends when ventral furrow formation becomes apparent. Duration at 25 degrees: approximately 40 minutes (130-170 minutes after egg laying).

name: BDC2.5/NOD
description: A mouse strain developed by selection for diabetes (high fasting blood glucose) from F6 of the CTS strain

name: BDC2.5/NOD
description: BDC2.5/NOD is a mouse strain as described in Jackson Laboratory http://jaxmice.jax.org/strain/004460.html

name: WW6
description: Embryonic stem cells isolated from mix of ~20% C57/B6J, ~75% 129/Sv and ~5% SJL all male strains.

name: Paranasal Sinus Schneiderian Papilloma
description: A papilloma that arises from the ciliated respiratory mucosa that lines the paranasal sinuses. It is classified as inverted papilloma and oncocytic papilloma.

name: Rectal Villous Adenoma
description: A neoplasm that arises from the glandular epithelium of the rectal mucosa. It is characterized by a villous architectural pattern. The neoplastic glandular cells have dysplastic features.

name: plasmodium parasite stage
description: The distinct stages of the life cycle of a protozoon of the genus Plasmodium.

name: neurodevelopmental disorder with seizures and non-epileptic hyperkinetic movements
description: An autosomal recessive, complex and progressive neurologic disorder characterized by severe neurodevelopmental delay and developmental regression, epileptic encephalopathy, postnatal microcephaly, hypotonia, and non-epileptic hyperkinetic movement disorder, including myoclonus dystonia, choreoathetosis, or generalized dyskinesia. Disease onset in infancy or first years of life.

name: reciprocal translocation
description: A type of chromosome rearrangement in which two nonhomologous chromosomes are each broken and then repaired in such a way that the resulting chromosomes each contain material from the other chromosome (a reciprocal translocation).

name: rostral anterior cingulate cortex volume measurement
description: Quantification of the volume of the rostral anterior cingulate cortex.

name: cancer site
description: Location of cancer, primary or metastatic

name: fractional shortening
description: A calculated measurement corresponding to the ratio or percent reduction in heart chamber diameter between end-systole and end-diastole.

name: cholelithiasis
description: The presence of calculi in the gallbladder.

name: cholelithiasis
description: Presence or formation of GALLSTONES in the BILIARY TRACT, usually in the gallbladder (CHOLECYSTOLITHIASIS) or the common bile duct (CHOLEDOCHOLITHIASIS).

name: eye morphology measurement
description: quantification of some aspect of eye morphology, such as the width of the eye socket

name: velopharyngeal dysfunction
description:
Velopharyngeal dysfunction (VPD) occurs when the muscular soft palate (velum) and lateral pharyngeal walls are physically unable to separate the oral and nasal cavities during speech production leading
to hypernasality and abnormal speech reduction.

name: CHGA cleavage product measurement
description: quantification of the amount of chromogranin A cleavage product in a sample

name: human granulocytic anaplasmosis
description: A tick-borne, infectious disease caused by Anaplasma phagocytophilum, an obligate intracellular bacterium that is typically transmitted to humans by ticks of the Ixodes ricinus species complex.

name: human granulocytic anaplasmosis
description: An ehrlichiosis that results_in infection located_in granular leukocyte, has_material_basis_in Anaplasma phagocytophilum, which is transmitted_by lone start tick (Amblyomma americanum ). The infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom muscle aches, has_symptom fatigue, has_symptom fever and has_symptom rash

name: cups of coffee per day measurement
description: the quantification of the number of cups of coffee that a subject consumes on average per day

name: obsolete_nose structure
description: 1a: The part of the face that bears the nostrils and covers the anterior part of the nasal cavity; broadly: this part together with the nasal cavity.n1b: The anterior part of the head at the top or end of the muzzle: snout, proboscis.n2: The vertebrate olfactory organ.

name: obsolete_nose structure
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that functions in (some) detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050907).

name: obsolete_nose structure
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that has function 'detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050907)'.

name: obsolete_nose structure
description: *Subdivision of face which consists of the nasal skeleton, nasal septum and nasal cavity.

name: obsolete_nose structure
description: 1a: The part of the face that bears the nostrils and covers the anterior part of the nasal cavity; broadly: this part together with the nasal cavity.nb: The anterior part of the head at the top or end of the muzzle: snout, proboscis.n2. The vertebrate olfactory organ.

name: plasma kallikrein measurement

name: glucose effectiveness measurement
description: quantification of glucose effectiveness, the capacity of glucose to enhance its own cellular uptake and to suppress endogenous glucose production

name: skin epithelioid hemangioma
description: Solitary or multiple benign cutaneous nodules comprised of immature and mature vascular structures intermingled with endothelial cells and a varied infiltrate of eosinophils, histiocytes, lymphocytes, and mast cells.

name: skin epithelioid hemangioma
description: A hemangioma arising from the skin. It is characterized by the presence of epithelioid endothelial cells.

name: Multiple Organ Failure
description: A progressive condition usually characterized by combined failure of several organs such as the lungs, liver, kidney, along with some clotting mechanisms, usually postinjury or postoperative.

name: tumor necrosis factor-inducible gene 6 protein measurement
description: quantification of the amount of tumor necrosis factor-inducible gene 6 protein in a sample

name: obsolete_neuromast
description: Volcano-shaped lateral line sensory organ located in characteristic positions within the skin epithelium and containing hair cells and their support elements. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

name: iDES
description: Integrated digital error suppression (iDES)

name: NG Capture-C
description: Next-generation capture-C

name: 17-hydroxyprogesterone
description: Quantification of the amount of 17-hydroxyprogesterone in a sample

name: dauer larva
description: C. elegans third stage larva specialized for dispersal and long term survival.

name: T98G
description: Human, Caucasian, glioblastoma cell line.

name: ES-E14TG2a.4
description: Feeder free cell line derived from E14TG2a.

name: obsessive-compulsive symptom measurement
description: quantification of some aspect of obsessive-compulsive symptoms, such as their existence and severity, usually via a standardised questionnaire or interview with a qualified mental health professional

name: 454 GS sequencer
description: The 454 GS is a GS high-throughput sequencing machine developed by 454 Life Sciences.

name: beta-lactam allergy measurement
description: Quantification of the presence or severity of an allergy to beta-lactam, including beta-lactam antibiotics.

name: CB1370
description: Strain of C. elegans, remarked as temperature sensitive dauer constitutive, maintan at 15C, 100% dauers at 25C. 15% dauer formation at 20C. Long-lived.

name: persistent oligoarticular juvenile idiopathic arthritis
description: Oligoarticular juvenile idiopathic arthritis affecting not more than 4 joints throughout the disease course.

name: compound based treatment
description: A treatment process in which a chemical compound is administered to the subject under investigation.

name: COLO 699
description: Human lung adenocarcinoma cell line (DSMZ catalog number ACC196)

name: Tis
description: Carcinoma in situ (CIS; abnormal cells are present but have not spread to neighboring tissue; although not cancer, CIS may become cancer and is sometimes called preinvasive cancer)

name: HCC1319
description: Human renal cell carcinoma cell line from 68-year-old Caucasian male

name: dental pulp exposure
description: The result of pathological changes in the hard tissue of a tooth caused by carious lesions, mechanical factors, or trauma, which render the pulp susceptible to bacterial invasion from the external environment.

name: DroNc-seq
description: Massively parallel sNuc-Seq with droplet technology

name: Pubic Symphysis Diastasis
description: Separation of the PUBIC SYMPHYSIS. It is an uncommon complication of CHILDBIRTH causing postpartum PAIN, but it can also arise from other causes.

name: tongue neoplasm
description: Tumors or cancer of the MOUTH.

name: tongue neoplasm
description: Tumors or cancer of the TONGUE.

name: menopause
description: The last menstrual period. Permanent cessation of menses (MENSTRUATION) is usually defined after 6 to 12 months of AMENORRHEA in a woman over 45 years of age. In the United States, menopause generally occurs in women between 48 and 55 years of age.

name: infant grey matter volume measurement
description: quantification of the volume of grey matter in an infant's brain

name: susceptibility to chronic sinus infection measurement
description: Quantification of an individual's susceptibility to chronic sinus infections, requiring surgery.

name: Guillain-Barre syndrome
description: Guillain-BarrC) syndrome (GBS) is the term used to describe a spectrum of rare post-infectious neuropathies that usually occur in otherwise healthy patients. GBS is clinically heterogeneous and encompasses acute inflammatory demyelinating polyradiculoneuropathy (AIDP), acute motor axonal neuropathy (AMAN) and acute motor-sensory axonal neuropathy (AMSAN), Miller-Fisher syndrome (MFS; see these terms) and some other regional variants.

name: Guillain-Barre syndrome
description: An autoimmune disease of peripheral nervous system that causes body's immune system to attack part of the peripheral nervous system.

name: embryonic stage 6
description: Stage 6 begins when the ventral furrow becomes apparent, an event which is followed rapidly by the formation of the cephalic furrow. Stage 6 ends when the pole cells have adopted a dorsal (horizontal) position at the posterior. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 10 minutes (170-180 minutes after egg laying).

name: TBP-71Q-16
description: TBP-71Q-16 is a mouse strain as described in Jackson Laboratory http://jaxmice.jax.org/strain/008216.html

name: ES-CJ7
description: Undifferentiated embryonic stem cells were originally isolated from 129S1/SVImJ strain mice by Swiatek PJ et al. in 1993.

name: Parathyroid Gland Carcinoma
description: A malignant tumor arising from the parenchymal cells of the parathyroid gland. It is associated with the symptoms of primary hyperparathyroidism, resulting from the excessive production of parathyroid hormone. Morphologically, the differential diagnosis from parathyroid gland adenoma may be difficult. A definitive diagnosis of carcinoma is made only in the presence of capsular invasion, vascular invasion, and/or perineural invasion.

name: Parathyroid Gland Carcinoma
description: Parathyroid carcinoma (PRTC) is a very rare, slow-growing, clinically serious endocrine tumor that generally develops in mid-adulthood. PRTC presents as a palpable painless mass in the neck and causes severe hypercalcemia and related symptoms, non-specific gastrointestinal manifestations, as well as renal and bone complications related to primary hyperparathyroidism (nephrolithiasis, impaired renal function, osteoporosis, bone pain, and pathologic fractures, etc.). Some PRTCs are however non-functioning tumors.

name: Renal Angiomyoadenomatous Tumor
description: A very rare, benign, encapsulated tumor that arises from the kidney. It is characterized by the presence of clear epithelial cells in a prominent smooth muscle stroma.

name: obsolete_endoderm
description: A germ layer lying remote from the surface of the embryo that gives rise to internal tissues such as gut.

name: O'Donnell-Luria-Rodan syndrome
description: A neurodevelopmental disorder characterized by global developmental delay, speech delay, intellectual disability and a subtle facial gestalt. Additional common features include autism, seizures, hypotonia and functional gastrointestinal abnormalities.

name: rostral middle frontal gyrus volume measurement
description: Quantification of the volume of the rostral middle frontal gyrus.

name: cortical thickness
description: Is a quantification of the thickness of brain cortex, e.g. measured by MRI, used in the diagnosis of Alzheimer's disease and other neurological conditions

name: heart relative wall thickness
description: A calculated measurement of heart wall geometry.  It represents a measure of the wall thickness normalized to the size of the chamber lumen.

name: response to interferon
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of any interferon stimulus

name: cell size selection
description: filtering process that either includes or excludes cells of a certain diameter using a physical filter

name: psychosocial stress measurement
description: the quantification of psychosocial stress factors such as financial strain, marital problems, work-related difficulties or health problems, usually assessed through self-reporting via standardised questionnaires.

name: plasma protease C1 inhibitor measurement
description: quantification of the amount of plasma protease C1 inhibitor in a sample

name: septic shock
description: Shock caused by infection; frequently caused by gram negative bacteria, although some cases have been caused by other bacteria, viruses, fungi, and protozoa; characterized by fever, chills, tachycardia, tachypnea, and hypotension. Shock is a state of acute circulatory failure characterized by persistent arterial hypotension despite adequate fluid resuscitation or by tissue hypoperfusion unexplained by other causes.

name: Mycoplasmatales Infections
description: Infections with bacteria of the order MYCOPLASMATALES.

name: tyrosine-protein kinase receptor Tie-1, soluble measurement
description: quantification of the amount of tyrosine-protein kinase receptor Tie-1, soluble in a sample

name: Skull Fractures
description: Fractures of the skull which may result from penetrating or nonpenetrating head injuries or rarely BONE DISEASES (see also FRACTURES, SPONTANEOUS). Skull fractures may be classified by location (e.g., SKULL FRACTURE, BASILAR), radiographic appearance (e.g., linear), or based upon cranial integrity (e.g., SKULL FRACTURE, DEPRESSED).

name: Ig-Seq
description: DNA sequencing of immunoglobulin genes (Ig-seq) for antibody repertoire determination

name: Non-Neoplastic Bile Duct Disorder
description: A non-neoplastic disorder that affects the intrahepatic or extrahepatic bile ducts. Representative examples include cholangitis and biliary atresia.

name: Nm-seq
description: Map 2′-O-methylation sites in human mRNA

name: systemising measurement
description: Quantification of the drive to systemise, ie identifiy input-operation-output relationships in order to build, analyse or understand systems, typically quantified by administration of a standardised questionnaire such as the Systemising Quotient-Revised (SQ-R)

name: L1 larva
description: C. elegans first stage larva. At 25 Centigrade, it ranges 14-25.5 hours after fertilization, 0-11.5 hours after hatch.

name: TIVE
description: TIVE is a human cell line.

name: VCaP
description: Human prostate cancer cell line.

name: Reticulocyte Corpuscular Hemoglobin Distribution Width
description: A measurement of the standard deviation of hemoglobin concentrations in reticulocytes, calculated as the standard deviation of hemoglobin content divided by the mean hemoglobin content. [ NCI ]

name: emotional symptom measurement
description: quantification of some aspect of emotional problem symptoms, such as their existence and severity, usually via a standardised questionnaire such as the emotional symptoms subscale of the Strengths and Difficulties Questionnaire or interview with a qualified mental health professional

name: differentiated
description: A property of a cell which is no longer pluripotent

name: obsolete_progeria syndrome
description: An abnormal congenital condition, associated with defects in the LAMIN TYPE A gene, which is characterized by premature aging in children, where all the changes of cell senescence occur. It is manifested by premature greying; hair loss; hearing loss (DEAFNESS); cataracts (CATARACT); ARTHRITIS; OSTEOPOROSIS; DIABETES MELLITUS; atrophy of subcutaneous fat; skeletal hypoplasia; elevated urinary HYALURONIC ACID; and accelerated ATHEROSCLEROSIS. Many affected individuals develop malignant tumors, especially SARCOMA.

name: obsolete_progeria syndrome
description: A very rare genetic disorder caused by mutations in the LMNA gene. It is characterized by premature aging. Signs and symptoms include failure to thrive, limited growth, alopecia, wrinkled skin, small face, development of atherosclerosis, and heart disease. There is no cure for this condition. Individuals do not usually survive beyond their early twenties. Death usually occurs as a result of complications from atherosclerosis.

name: household income
description: A demographic parameter indicating the amount of earning made by a family.

name: extended oligoarticular juvenile idiopathic arthritis
description: Oligoarticular juvenile idiopathic arthritis affecting a total of more than 4 joints after the first 6 months of disease.

name: COLO 741
description: Derived from a pelvic wall metastasis of a 69 year old female with colon carcinoma. (Sigma-Aldrich catalog number 93052621)

name: TX
description: A stage in which the tumor cannot be evaluated

name: HCC1482
description: Human uterine adenocarcinoma cell line from 62-year-old Caucasian female

name: caMAB-seq
description: 5caC methylase-assisted bisulfite sequencing (caMAB-seq)

name: desmoplastic fibroma
description: A extremely rare bone tumor characterized by abundant collagen formation and a fibrous stroma, without evidence of mitosis or pleomorphism. It appears on x-rays as an osteolytic lesion with well-defined margins and must be differentiated from primary fibrosarcoma of bone. (DeVita Jr et al., Cancer: Principles & Practice of Oncology, 3d ed, p1441)

name: Drop-ChIP
description: Droplet-based single-cell ChIP-seq (Drop-ChIP)

name: pulmonary aspergillosis
description: A aspergillosis that involves the lung.

name: pulmonary aspergillosis
description: Infections of the respiratory tract with fungi of the genus ASPERGILLUS. Infections may result in allergic reaction (ALLERGIC BRONCHOPULMONARY ASPERGILLOSIS), colonization in pulmonary cavities as fungus balls (MYCETOMA), or lead to invasion of the lung parenchyma (INVASIVE PULMONARY ASPERGILLOSIS).

name: colitis
description: Inflammation of the colon.

name: colitis
description: Inflammation of the COLON section of the large intestine (INTESTINE, LARGE), usually with symptoms such as DIARRHEA (often with blood and mucus), ABDOMINAL PAIN, and FEVER.

name: bone density
description: The amount of mineral per square centimeter of BONE. This is the definition used in clinical practice. Actual bone density would be expressed in grams per milliliter. It is most frequently measured by X-RAY ABSORPTIOMETRY or TOMOGRAPHY, X RAY COMPUTED. Bone density is an important predictor for OSTEOPOROSIS.

name: response to high sodium diet
description: physiological response of an organism, eg in terms of blood pressure, to being fed a diet high in sodium

name: infant intracranial volume measurement
description: quantification of an infant's intracranial volume

name: embryonic stage 7
description: Stage 7 begins when the pole cells have adopted a dorsal (horizontal) position at the posterior. Invagination of the anterior and posterior midgut and hindgut follows. The 'discoid plate' that carries the pole cells forms a pocket. Transverse furrows (dorsal folds) form on the dorsal surface. This stage ends when the anterior wall of the amnioproctodeal invagination starts moving anteriorly and the pole cells are no longer visible externally. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 10 minutes (180-190 minutes after egg laying).

name: CB6F1
description: CB6F1 is a mouse strain as described in Jackson Laboratory http://jaxmice.jax.org/strain/100007.html

name: Parathyroid Hyperplasia
description: Parathyroid hyperplasia is the enlargement of all four parathyroid glands. The parathyroid glands are glands in the neck that produce parathyroid hormone (PTH). (https://www.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/ency/article/001189.htm)

name: Parathyroid Hyperplasia
description: A hyperplasia that involves the parathyroid gland.

name: Renal Cell Carcinoma Associated with Xp11.2 Translocations/TFE3 Gene Fusions
description: A group of kidney carcinomas characterized by the presence of different translocations involving the chromosome Xp11.2. These translocations result in the creation of gene fusions involving the TFE3 gene. Patients are usually children and young adults. Morphologically, the malignant epithelial cells form papillary patterns. The clinical behavior of this group of carcinomas is largely unknown.

name: Renal Cell Carcinoma Associated with Xp11.2 Translocations/TFE3 Gene Fusions
description: A group of kidney carcinomas characterized by the presence of different translocations involving the chromosome Xp11.2. These translocations result in the creation of gene fusions involving the TFE3 gene. Patients are usually children and young adults. Morphologically, the malignant epithelial cells form papillary patterns.

name: abnormal glucose tolerance
description: An abnormal resistance to glucose, i.e., a reduction in the ability to maintain glucose levels in the blood stream within normal limits following oral or intravenous administration of glucose.

name: Shukla-Vernon syndrome
description: A X-linked neurodevelopmental disorder manifesting in affected males with intellectual and learning disability, motor and language delay, autism spectrum disorder, attention deficit and hyperactivity disorder, and dysmorphic features. Some patients may have seizures and/or cerebellar atrophy on brain imaging. Carrier females may have mild disease manifestations.

name: translocation
description: A type of chromosome rearrangement in which two nonhomologous chromosomes are each broken and then repaired

name: CD40 ligand measurement
description:
Is a quantification of CD40 ligand,  primarily expressed on activated CD4+ T lymphocytes. Protein function - mediates B-cell proliferation in the absence of co-stimulus as well as IgE production in the presence of IL-4. Involved in immunoglobulin class switching.1 Publication
Release of soluble CD40L from platelets is partially regulated by GP IIb/IIIa, actin polymerization, and an matrix metalloproteinases (MMP) inhibitor-sensitive pathway.

name: superior frontal gyrus volume measurement
description: Quantification of the volume of the superior frontal gyrus.

name: digit length ratio
description: Is the ratio of 2D:4D used a a marker for prenatal androgen exposure.

name: interventricular septum thickness
description: A quantitative measurement of the thickness of an interventricular septum.

name: Epstein-Barr virus early antigen seropositivity
description: The result of a measurement of circulating Epstein-Barr virus early antigen-specific antibodies

name: body height at birth
description: The distance from the sole to the crown of the head of a newborn right after birth

name: platelet glycoprotein 4 measurement
description: quantification of the amount of platelet glycoprotein 4 in a sample

name: pyoderma gangrenosum
description: An idiopathic, rapidly evolving, and severely debilitating disease occurring most commonly in association with chronic ulcerative colitis. It is characterized by the presence of boggy, purplish ulcers with undermined borders, appearing mostly on the legs. The majority of cases are in people between 40 and 60 years old. Its etiology is unknown.

name: Myocardial Ischemia
description: A disorder of cardiac function caused by insufficient blood flow to the muscle tissue of the heart. The decreased blood flow may be due to narrowing of the coronary arteries (CORONARY ARTERY DISEASE), to obstruction by a thrombus (CORONARY THROMBOSIS), or less commonly, to diffuse narrowing of arterioles and other small vessels within the heart. Severe interruption of the blood supply to the myocardial tissue may result in necrosis of cardiac muscle (MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION).

name: Myocardial Ischemia
description: A disorder of cardiac function caused by insufficient blood flow to the muscle tissue of the heart. The decreased blood flow may be due to narrowing of the coronary arteries (coronary artery disease), to obstruction by a thrombus (coronary thrombosis), or less commonly, to diffuse narrowing of arterioles and other small vessels within the heart. Severe interruption of the blood supply to the myocardial tissue may result in necrosis of cardiac muscle (myocardial infarction).

name: UMP-CMP kinase measurement
description: quantification of the amount of UMP-CMP kinase in a sample

name: lung structure
description: A lung structuret is a respiratory system component which is part of a lung.

name: Spinal Cord Ischemia
description: Reduced blood flow to the spinal cord which is supplied by the anterior spinal artery and the paired posterior spinal arteries. This condition may be associated with ARTERIOSCLEROSIS, trauma, emboli, diseases of the aorta, and other disorders. Prolonged ischemia may lead to INFARCTION of spinal cord tissue.

name: Spinal Cord Ischemia
description: Reduced blood flow to the spinal cord which is supplied by the anterior spinal artery and the paired posterior spinal arteries. This condition may be associated with arteriosclerosis, trauma, emboli, diseases of the aorta, and other disorders. Prolonged ischemia may lead to infarction of spinal cord tissue.

name: obsolete_paraxial mesoderm
description: Mesoderm which is lateral to the neural tube on both sides.

name: Malignant Bone Neoplasm
description: A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm affecting the bone or articular cartilage.

name: IMS-MDA
description: Immunomagnetic separation for targeted bacterial enrichment for MDA (IMS-MDA)

name: Non-Seminomatous Lesion
description: A group of testicular cancers that begin in the germ cells (cells that give rise to sperm). Nonseminomas are identified by the type of cell in which they begin and include embryonal carcinoma, teratoma, choriocarcinoma, and yolk sac carcinoma.

name: NOIR
description: Non-overlapping integrated reads (NOIR)

name: ceramide measurement
description: A quantification of ceramides.

name: L4 larva
description: C. elegans fourth stage larva. At 25 Centigrade, it ranges 40-49.5 hours after fertilization, 26-35.5 hours after hatch.

name: rosacea severity measurement
description: Quantification of the severity of rosacea symptoms, based on a survey of facial, nose and ocular sympoms related to rosacea, a chronic inflammatory skin disease.

name: fibrosarcoma
description: A benign, intermediate, or malignant mesenchymal neoplasm characterized by the presence of neoplastic fibroblasts.

name: seasonal gut microbiome measurement
description: quantification of some aspect of the seasonal variation in the micrbiome of the gut

name: emphysematous cholecystitis
description: Cholecystitis resulting from infection by gas producing organisms.

name: emphysematous cholecystitis
description: Emphysematous cholecystitis is a bacterial infectious disease consisting of an inflammation of the gallbladder characterized by air-filled expansions in interstitial or subcutaneous tissues.

name: Reticulocyte Hemoglobin Distribution Width
description: A measurement of the distribution of the hemoglobin concentration in reticulocytes. [ NCI ]

name: LDL cholesterol change measurement
description: quantification of the change in LDL cholesterol levels in an individual over time, eg over the course of several hours after a high-fat meal or following treatment with a cholesterol-lowering drug

name: 454 GS FLX Titanium sequencer
description: The 454 GS FLX Titanium sequencer is a GS high-throughput sequencing machine developed by 454 Life Sciences.

name: prognostic subgroup
description: A population in which a grouping of subjects in some study grouped on the basis of the probable outcome of some disease e.g. by gene expression, by physiological indicators etc

name: obsolete_time to development of distant metastases
social deprivation
description: Absence of social environment which is necessary for the social development of the individual.

name: GM25256
description: Induced pluripotent stem cell line derived from adult skin (leg) fibroblasts; subject clinically normal; wild-type; FISH test: 46, XY.

name: obsolete_hypoblast
description: The inner of the two layers of the blastoderm that forms during gastrulation and give rise to the definitive mesoderm and endoderm.

name: obsolete_hypoblast
description: The inner of the two layers of the blastoderm that forms during gastrulation and give rise to the definitive mesoderm and endoderm. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: COLO 783
description: Human melanoma cell line (DSMZ catalog number ACC257)

name: clinical temporal measurement
description: A temporal measurement related to disease progression

name: HCC1493
description: Human breast adenocarcinoma cell line from 43-year-old male patient

name: CAP-seq
description: CXXC affinity purification plus deep sequencing (CAP-seq)

name: diffuse cutaneous Leishmaniasis
description: A form of LEISHMANIASIS, CUTANEOUS caused by Leishmania aethiopica in Ethiopia and Kenya, L. pifanoi in Venezuela, L. braziliensis in South America, and L. mexicana in Central America. This disease is characterized by massive dissemination of skin lesions without visceral involvement.

name: M14
description: The human melanoma cell line M14 has been established from surgically removed melanoma metastases.

name: Drop-seq
description: Analyze mRNA transcripts from individual cells in droplets (Drop-seq)

name: obsolete_spinal muscular atrophy with respiratory distress
hair color
description: Color of hair or fur.

name: response to low sodium diet
description: physiological response of an organism, eg in terms of blood pressure, to being fed a diet low in sodium

name: blastic plasmacytoid dendritic cell neoplasm
description: A clinically aggressive neoplasm derived from the precursors of plasmacytoid dendritic cells (also called professional type I interferon-producing cells or plasmacytoid monocytes), with a high frequency of cutaneous and bone marrow involvement and leukemic dissemination. (WHO 2017) [ NCI ]

name: hand, foot and mouth disease
description: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection located_in skin, has_material_basis_in Human coxsackievirus A16 or has_material_basis_in Human enterovirus 71, which are transmitted_by contaminated fomites, and transmitted_by contact with nose and throat secretions, saliva, blister fluid and stool of infected persons. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom poor appetite, has_symptom malaise, has_symptom sore throat, has_symptom painful sores in the mouth, and has_symptom skin rash on the palms of the hands and soles of the feet.

name: hand, foot and mouth disease
description: A clinical syndrome that is usually caused by enterovirus infection, and that is characterized by fever, anorexia, and painful sores in the mouth, distal extremities, and/or other sites, including the buttocks.

name: osteoprotegerin measurement
description: quantification of osteoprotegerin in a sample

name: Parotid Gland Acinic Cell Carcinoma
description: An adenocarcinoma with serous acinar cell differentiation that arises from the parotid gland. Patients usually present with a slow growing mass in the parotid area.

name: Retinal Neoplasm
description: A benign or malignant neoplasm affecting the retina. Representative examples of benign neoplasms include retinocytoma and hemangioma. Representative examples of malignant neoplasms include retinoblastoma, lymphoma and melanoma.

name: family history of cancer
description: A form of clinicaly history specifically about cancer in family members.

name: GIST-plus syndrome
description: A disorder characterized by multiple mesenchymal tumors of the gastrointestinal tract, including gastrointestinal stromal tumor, inflammatory fibroid polyps, and fibroid tumors. Additional features are coarse facies and skin, broad hands and feet, and premature tooth loss. GISTPS is an autosomal dominant disease with incomplete penetrance. Gastrointestinal stromal tumor and inflammatory fibroid polyps may also occur in isolation.

name: AA86
description: C. elegans Daf-d, weak heterochronic phenotypes in seam, somatic gonad, intestine. Class III allele.

name: tissue plasminogen activator measurement
description: Is a quantification of tissue plasminogen activator, an enzyme which converts the abundant, but inactive, zymogen plasminogen to plasmin by hydrolyzing a single Arg-Val bond in plasminogen. By controlling plasmin-mediated proteolysis, it plays an important role in tissue remodeling and degradation, in cell migration and many other physiopathological events. Play a direct role in facilitating neuronal migration.

name: antibody
description: An antibody function (or antigen binding function) is an infection-fighting protein molecule in blood or secretory fluids that tags, neutralizes, and helps destroy pathogenic microorganisms such as bacteria, viruses and toxins.

name: eosinophil count
description: The number of granulocytes (polymorphonuclear leukocytes) in a specified volume of blood, usually 1 cubic millimeter.

name: eosinophil count
description: Is a quantification of eosinphils in blood.

name: antidepressant-induced side effect
description: any sign or symptom that is the direct result of treatment with antidepressant medication

name: posterior wall thickness
description: A quantitative measurement of the thickness or depth of the dorsal/posterior wall of the heart.

name: Herpes simplex virus 2 seropositivity
description: The result of a measurement of circulating Herpes simplex virus 2-specific antibodies

name: infant body height
description: The distance from the sole to the crown of the head of an infant, which can be used as a proxy for skeletal growth in early life

name: platelet glycoprotein VI measurement
description: quantification of the amount of platelet glycoprotein VI in a sample

name: rapid kidney function decline
description: decline in kidney function defined as a decline in glomerular filtration rate in one year of  > 3 ml/min per 1.73m2

name: Necrobiotic Xanthogranuloma
description: A cutaneous necrobiotic disorder characterized by firm, yellow plaques or nodules, often in a periorbital distribution. It is often accompanied by an elevated ERYTHROCYTE SEDIMENTATION RATE; LEUKOPENIA; and MONOCLONAL GAMMOPATHY (IgG-kappa type) and systemic involvement.

name: Necrobiotic Xanthogranuloma
description: A cutaneous necrobiotic disorder characterized by firm, yellow plaques or nodules, often in a periorbital distribution. It is often accompanied by an elevated erythrocyte sedimentation rate; leukopenia; and monoclonal gammopathy (IgG-kappa type) and systemic involvement.

name: vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 2 measurement
description: quantification of the amount of vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 2 in a sample

name: serum carcinoembryonic antigen measurement
description: Quantification of carcinoembryonic antigen in serum. Carcinoembryonic antigen is a cancer-specific antigen associated with both tumors and the developing fetus. The main use of this antigen is as a tumor marker, especially with respect to intestinal cancers. Production of the antigen ceases shortly before birth, but may reappear in people who develop certain types of cancer.

name: in-cell SHAPE-Seq
description: Combines in-cell probing of RNA structure with a measurement of gene expression to simultaneously characterize RNA structure and function in bacterial cells

name: Normal Breast-Like Subtype of Breast Carcinoma
description: A biologic subset of breast carcinoma defined by high expression of many genes expressed by adipose and other non-epithelial tissues.

name: DNA library construction
description: A DNA library is constructed from DNA extracted from cells.

name: diglyceride measurement
description: A quantification of diglycerides.

name: growth differentiation factor 15 measurement
description: Quantification of growth differentiation factor 15 in a biological sample.

name: response to immunochemotherapy
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an immunochemotherapy stimulus.

name: Blast Count
description: The determination of the number of blast cells present in a blood sample. [ NCI ]

name: aortitis
description: Inflammation of the wall of the AORTA.

name: aortitis
description: Inflammation of the aorta. Causes include trauma, infectious disorders, and connective tissue disorders.

name: HDL cholesterol change measurement
description: quantification of the change in HDL cholesterol levels in an individual over time, eg over the course of several hours after a high-fat meal or following treatment with a cholesterol-lowering drug

name: 454 GS Junior sequencer
description: The 454 GS Junior is a GS high-throughput sequencing machine developed by 454 Life Sciences.

name: timepoint
description: Time point at which a sample or observation is made or taken from a biomaterial as measured from some reference point.

name: pathological complete response
description: The disappearance of all signs of cancer, supported by pathological examination.

name: Exanthema Subitum
description: An acute, short-lived, viral disease of infants and young children characterized by a high fever at onset that drops to normal after 3-4 days and the concomitant appearance of a macular or maculopapular rash that appears first on the trunk and then spreads to other areas. It is the sixth of the classical exanthematous diseases and is caused by HHV-6; (HERPESVIRUS 6, HUMAN). (From Dorland, 27th ed)

name: Exanthema Subitum
description: An infection that is due to human herpesvirus (HHV) types 6 or 7; it is characterized by 3-5 days of high fever followed by the acute onset of a rosy, pink, non-pruritic, macular rash that is predominantly on the neck and trunk.

name: response to ketamine
description: Any change in the state of an organism as a result of a ketamine stimulus. Ketamine is a selective antagonist of the NMDA receptor, used primarily in anaesthesia, sedation and pain management.

name: obsolete_hypocotyl
description: The part of the axis of a plant embryo or seedling below the cotyledon.

name: COLO 792
description: Derived from a brain metastasis of a 62 year old male with melanoma. The cells bleb during culture. (Sigma-Aldrich catalog number 93052616)

name: HCC1534
description: Human lung adenocarcinoma cell line

name: Capp-Seq
description: Cancer personalized profiling by deep sequencing (CAPP-Seq)

name: diffuse esophageal spasm
description: A hypermotility disorder of the ESOPHAGUS that is characterized by spastic non-peristaltic responses to SWALLOWING; CHEST PAIN; and DYSPHAGIA.

name: obsolete_mediastinum
description: A group of organs surrounded by loose connective tissue, separating the two pleural sacs, between the sternum anteriorly and the vertebral column posteriorly as well as from the thoracic inlet superiorly to the diaphragm inferiorly. The mediastinum contains the heart and pericardium, the bases of the great vessels, the trachea and bronchi, esophagus, thymus, lymph nodes, thoracic duct, phrenic and vagus nerves, and other structures and tissues.

name: Droplet-CirSeq
description: Ultra-precise detection of mutations by droplet-based amplification of circularized DNA

name: pyogenic liver abscess
description: Single or multiple areas of PUS due to bacterial infection within the hepatic parenchyma. It can be caused by a variety of BACTERIA, local or disseminated from infections elsewhere such as in APPENDICITIS; CHOLECYSTITIS; PERITONITIS; and after LIVER TRANSPLANTATION.

name: essential tremor
description: A movement disorder that causes involuntary tremors, especially in the hands. It occurs alone without other neurological signs and symptoms.

name: flatfoot
description: An anatomic deformity in which the arch of the foot collapses, resulting in the entire sole of the foot coming into complete or near-complete contact with the ground.

name: flatfoot
description: A condition in which one or more of the arches of the foot have flattened out.

name: cognition
description: Intellectual or mental process whereby an organism becomes aware of or obtains knowledge.

name: response to dietary potassium supplementation
description: physiological response of an organism to being given potassium as a dietary supplement

name: rosacea
description: A chronic erythematous skin disorder that affects the face. It is characterized by the development of redness in the cheeks, nose, and/or forehead and telangiectasia. Sometimes, the erythematous changes may involve the eyelids.

name: rosacea
description: a chronic skin condition characterized by facial redness, small and superficial dilated blood vessels on facial skin, papules, pustules, and swelling.

name: Ara-C-resistant murine leukemia
description:
An Ara-C-resistant murine leukemia is a cell line.
A b117h, and a b140h are kinds of Ara-C-resistant murine leukemias.

name: anterior uveitis
description: Inflammation of the iris and anterior chamber of the eye.

name: anterior uveitis
description: Inflammation of the anterior uvea comprising the iris, angle structures, and the ciliary body. Manifestations of this disorder include ciliary injection, exudation into the anterior chamber, iris changes, and adhesions between the iris and lens (posterior synechiae). Intraocular pressure may be increased or reduced.

name: organophosphate poisoning
description: Poisoning due to organophosphates (a class of organophosphorus compounds also known as phosphate esters, or OPEs). Organophosphates are used as insecticides, medications, and nerve agents. Symptoms include increased saliva and tear production, diarrhea, vomiting, small pupils, sweating, muscle tremors, and confusion.

name: Hantavirus infectious disease
description: Any infection caused by a virus of the genus Hantavirus, which is transmitted by aerosolized rodent excreta or rodent bites, that can result in a variety of clinical manifestations from hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome to a pulmonary syndrome.

name: Hantavirus infectious disease
description: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection, located_in lungs or located_in kidney, has_material_basis_in Hantavirus, which is transmitted_by rodents. The infection has_symptom renal failure, has_symptom hemorrhagic manifestations, and has_symptom pulmonary edema.

name: embryonic stage 8
description: Stage 8 starts with the rapid phase of germ band extension and ends with the beginning of mesodermal segmentation. By the end of this stage germ band extension has progressed to the point where the proctodeal opening is at about 60% egg length and the dorsal folds (transverse furrows) are no longer visible. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 30 minutes (190-220 minutes after egg laying).

name: recombination measurement
description: quantification of any recombination-related factor, such as hotspot usage, African enchrichment and recombination rate

name: Parotid Gland Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma
description: An aggressive carcinoma that arises from the parotid gland. It is characterized by the presence of malignant epithelial and myoepithelial cells forming cribriform, tubular, and solid patterns. It usually presents as a slow growing mass. Patients develop pain because of the tendency of these carcinomas to invade perineural tissues.

name: visual memory measurement
description: Quantification of an individual's ability to store and recall visual information.

name: malaise
description: A feeling of general discomfort or uneasiness, an out-of-sorts feeling. [def-source: NCI][attr: CDC Glossary]

name: obsolete_endothelium
description: Single pavement layer of cells which line the luminal surface of the entire vascular system and regulate the transport of macromolecules and blood components from interstitium to lumen; this function has been most intensively studied in the blood capillaries.

name: obsolete_endothelium
description: A layer of epithelium that lines the heart, blood vessels (ENDOTHELIUM, VASCULAR), lymph vessels (ENDOTHELIUM, LYMPHATIC), and the serous cavities of the body.

name: AA87
description: C. elegans Daf-c, gonadal Mig, weak heterochronic phenotypes in intestine and seam. Class VI allele.

name: plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 measurement
description: Is a quantification of plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 a serine protease inhibitor. This inhibitor acts as 'bait' for tissue plasminogen activator, urokinase, protein C and matriptase-3/TMPRSS7. Its rapid interaction with PLAT may function as a major control point in the regulation of fibrinolysis

name: obsolete_aorta
description: The main trunk of the systemic arteries.

name: obsolete_aorta
description: Principal unpaired, median artery of the trunk, leading from the paired roots (radices) of the dorsal aorta to the caudal artery. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: obsolete_aorta
description: The great arterial trunk that carries blood from the heart to be distributed by branch arteries through the body.

name: obsolete_aorta
description: Principal unpaired, median artery of the trunk, leading from the paired roots (radices) of the dorsal aorta to the caudal artery.

name: obsolete_aorta
description: The major arterial trunk that carries oxygenated blood from the left ventricle into the ascending aorta behind the heart, the aortic arch, through the thorax as the descending aorta and through the abdomen as the abdominal aorta; it bifurcates into the left and right common iliac arteries.

name: AG04450
description: The culture was initiated on 5/20/80 from explants of minced lung tissue taken from a therapeutically aborted fetus of 12 weeks gestational age. The cell morphology is fibroblast-like. The karyotype is 46,XY; normal diploid male. A matched skin-derived fibroblast culture from same fetus is AG04449.

name: vitamin B measurement
description: Is a quantification of any or all of the B vitamins

name: antidepressant-induced dizziness
description: dizziness that is the direct result of treatment with antidepressant medication

name: left ventricular mass
description: A quantitative measure calculated as the difference between the epicardium delimited volume and the left ventricular chamber volume

name: platelet-derived growth factor BB measurement
description: quantification of the amount of platelet-derived growth factor BB in a sample

name: Neisseriaceae Infections
description: Infections with bacteria of the family NEISSERIACEAE.

name: vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 3 measurement
description: quantification of the amount of vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 3 in a sample

name: Subacute Combined Degeneration
description: A neuropathy due to VITAMIN B 12 DEFICIENCY or to excessive NITROUS OXIDE inhalation. It is associated with overproduction of the myelinolytic TUMOR NECROSIS FACTOR-ALPHA.

name: obsolete_presumptive ectoderm
description: Presumptive structure at the animal poll of the blastula that will develop into ectoderm via the epiblast. Determined by fate mapping.

name: Malignant Germ Cell Tumor
description: A gonadal or extragonadal malignant neoplasm that arises from germ cells. Representative examples include embryonal carcinoma, yolk sac tumor, and seminoma.

name: Ocular Melanoma
description: A melanoma that arises from the structures of the eye or ocular adnexa.

name: oophorectomy
description: The surgical removal of an ovary or ovaries.

name: lysophosphatidylcholine measurement
description: A quantification of lysophosphatidylcholines.

name: psychotic symptom measurement
description: Quantification of some aspect of psychotic symptoms, such as their existence and severity, usually via a standardised questionnaire or interview with a qualified mental health professional. The symptoms can include paranoia, hallucinations, anhedonia, cognitive disorganisation.

name: atopic march
description: sequential manifestations of different allergic diseases such as eczema, asthma and rhinitis. Typically, eczema is the first allergic disease in infancy, followed by asthma and/or rhinitis in childhood.

name: Blood Cell Count Ratio Measurement
description: The determination of the ratio of one blood cell component lto another in a blood sample. The measurement may be expressed as either a ratio or a percentage. [ NCI ]

name: total cholesterol change measurement
description: quantification of the change in total cholesterol levels in an individual over time, eg over the course of several hours after a high-fat meal or following treatment with a cholesterol-lowering drug

name: 2102Ep
description: 2102ep is an embryonal cell line

name: PA-TU-8988S
description: human pancreatic adenocarcinoma cell line from a 64 year old female

name: Arterio-Arterial Fistula
description: Abnormal communication between two ARTERIES that may result from injury or occur as a congenital abnormality.

name: gestational blood glucose measurement
description: Quantification of glucose levels in the blood of a pregnant individual.

name: age at first sexual intercourse measurement
description: A measurement of the age at which a person has the first sexual intercourse.

name: obsolete_hypopharynx
description: The lower part of the pharynx that connects to the esophagus.

name: obsolete_hypopharynx
description: The portion of the pharynx that lies below the upper edge of the epiglottis and opens into the larynx and esophagus.

name: obsolete_hypopharynx
description: The hypopharynx is part of the pharynx that lies below the upper edge of the epiglottis and opens into the larynx and esophagus.

name: COLO 800
description: Derived from a subcutaneous nodule of a tumour from a 14-year-old male. Cells display remarkable blebbing. (Sigma-Aldrich catalog number 93051123)

name: HCC1576
description: Human adrenal gland tumour cell line

name: CapSeq
description: 5’ anchored profiling of Pol II transcripts (CapSeq). Identifies pre-mRNAs, transspliced mRNAs, miRNAs, and noncoding RNAs

name: erythroplasia
description: A condition of the mucous membrane characterized by erythematous papular lesions. (Dorland, 27th ed)

name: DSB-seq
description: Map DNA double-strand breaks

name: rectocele
description: Herniation of the RECTUM into the VAGINA.

name: neuropsychological test
description: Tests designed to assess neurological function associated with certain behaviors. They are used in diagnosing brain dysfunction or damage and central nervous system disorders or injury.

name: response to cold pressor test
description: physiological response, in terms of blood pressure, heart rate or pain, to a cardiovascular test performed by immersing the hand into ice water, usually for one minute

name: Morton Neuroma
description: Swelling and inflammation of the nerve between the ends of the metatarsal bones at the base of the toes. It is caused by compression of the nerve, usually between the third and fourth toes. It results in a burning, sharp pain and numbness on the bottom of the foot in the area involved. Symptoms may resolve by resting the foot, taking anti-inflammatory drugs, applying ice packs, or injecting cortisone at the site. Persistent symptoms require surgical excision of the affected nerve. [def-source: NCI]

name: embryonic stage 9
description: Stage 9 begins when mesodermal segmentation becomes (transiently) visible\, and ends with the appearance of the stomodeal invagination slightly ventral to the anterior pole. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 40 minutes (220-260 minutes after egg laying).

name: verbal memory measurement
description: Quantification of an individual's ability to store and recall linguistic information.

name: follow-up
description: The process by which information about the health status of an individual is obtained after a study has officially closed; an activity that continues something that has already begun or that repeats something that has already been done. [def-source: NCI]

name: AA89
description: C. elegans daf-c. Gonald Mig. Weak heterochronic phenotypes in intestine. Class VI allele.

name: ARPE-19
description: ARPE-19 is a spontaneously arising retinal pigment epithelia (RPE) cell line derived in 1986 by Amy Aotaki-Keen from the normal eyes of a 19-year-old male who died from head trauma in a motor vehicle accident.

name: hip bone size
description: Is a quantification of the size of a human hip bone.

name: obsolete_cardiac ventricle
description: One of four heart chambers.

name: obsolete_cardiac ventricle
description: Cavitated compound organ that receives blood flow from the atrium and delivers blood to the body via the aorta. Valves are present to direct flow. There are only two chambers present in the fish heart.

name: obsolete_cardiac ventricle
description: General anatomical term which refers to a chamber of an organ with cavitated organ parts. Examples: right ventricle of heart, lateral ventricle of brain.

name: obsolete_cardiac ventricle
description: The lower right and left chambers of the heart. The right pumps venous blood into the lungs and the left pumps oxygenated blood into the systemic arterial circulation. (MeSH)

name: obsolete_cardiac ventricle
description: A chamber of the heart which receives blood from a corresponding atrium and from which blood is forced into the arteries.

name: antidepressant-induced sexual dysfunction
description: sexual dysfunction such as loss of sexual desire that is the direct result of treatment with antidepressant medication

name: HM7
description: human colon adenocarcinoma cell line

name: platelet-derived growth factor receptor beta measurement
description: quantification of the amount of platelet-derived growth factor receptor beta in a sample

name: vaso-occlusive pain measurement
description: quantification of some aspect of vaso-occlusive pain, or vas-occlusive crises, such as severity or frequency of occurences

name: Subdural Effusion
description: Leakage and accumulation of CEREBROSPINAL FLUID in the subdural space which may be associated with an infectious process; CRANIOCEREBRAL TRAUMA; BRAIN NEOPLASMS; INTRACRANIAL HYPOTENSION; and other conditions.

name: neuropathic pain
description: Chronic pain caused by damage to nerve fibers. It is usually associated with tissue injury.

name: Malignant Jugulotympanic Paraganglioma
description: A jugulotympanic paraganglioma that metastasizes to other anatomic sites.

name: Ocular Melanoma with Extraocular Extension
description: https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&code=C7913&ns=NCI_Thesaurus

name: tonsillectomy
description: A surgical procedure in which both palatine tonsils are fully removed from the back of the throat.

name: lysophosphatidylethanolamine measurement
description: A quantification of lysophosphatidylethanolamines.

name: obsolete_T lymphocyte
description: A cell of the B cell, T cell, or natural killer cell lineage.

name: empathy measurement
description: Quantification of some aspect of empathy, i.e. the ability to understand and share another person's experiences and emotions

name: Staphylococcus aureus carrier status
description: quantification of the presence or absence of Staphylococcus aureus colonies in an individual. Positive carrier status should not be equated with infection.

name: Blood Cell Count with Differential
description: A hematologic procedure to determine the number of red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets, including the white cell differential count and red cell morphology, in a blood sample. [ NCI ]

name: erythrocyte cadmium measurement
description: Quantification of the amount of cadmium present in erythrocytes. Cadmium in erythrocytes is a valid biomarker of exposure and body burden of cadmium, a non-essential toxic metal with multiple adverse health effects

name: experimental cell
description: experimental cell is a cell which is experimentally derived such as a cell line cell, or a cell differentiated in culture. Experimentally derived cells may have diffrent properties from the cell from which they originally derived, such as through gene expression changes.

name: obsolete_protocol factor
description: A protocol factor is an experimental factor which describes factors that describe the protocol design of an experiment.

name: NCI-H2452
description: human lung mesothelioma cell line (ATCC CRL-5946)

name: transfection
description: The process of bringing about genetic alteration of any cell or organism by a variety of means including recombinant DNA technology, viruses, chemical mutagens and X-rays.

name: obsolete_PA-TU-8988T
description: human pancreatic adenocarcinoma cell line established in 1985 from the liver metastasis of a primary pancreatic adenocarcinoma from a 64-year-old woman (DSMZ catalog number ACC 162)

name: Atrophic Vaginitis
description: Inflammation of the vagina due to thinning of the vaginal wall and decreased lubrication associated with reduced estrogen levels at MENOPAUSE.

name: foot muscle strength measurement
description: Quantification of foot muscle strength.

name: Eye Foreign Bodies
description: Inanimate objects that become enclosed in the eye.

name: COLO 849
description: derived in 1992 from right axillary lymph nodes of a 43-year-old Caucasian man with metastatic maligant melanoma (DSMZ catalog number ACC 216)

name: Capture-HiC

description: Peripheral T-cell Lymphoma Not Otherwise Specified(PTCL NOS) refers to a group of diseases that do not fit into any of the other subtypes of PTCL. PTCL-NOS is the most common PTCL subtype, making up about one quarter of all PTCLs. It is also the most common of all the T-cell lymphomas. The term PTCL can be confusing as it can refer to the entire spectrum of mature T-cell lymphomas, but it can also refer to the specific PTCL-NOS subtype. Although most patients with PTCL-NOS are diagnosed with their disease confined to the lymph nodes, sites outside the lymph nodes, such as the liver, bone marrow, gastrointestinal tract, and skin, may also be involved. This group of PTCLs is aggressive and requires combination chemotherapy upon diagnosis.

name: obsolete_vomeronasal organ
description: The vomeronasal organ (VNO), or Jacobson's organ, is an auxiliary olfactory sense organ that is found in many animals. It was discovered by Ludwig Jacobson in 1813. During embryological development, it forms from the nasal (olfactory) placode, at the anterior edge of the neural plate. It is a chemoreceptor organ which is completely separated from the nasal cavity the majority of the time, being enclosed in a separate bony or cartilaginous capsule which opens into the base of the nasal cavity. It is a tubular crescent shape and split into two pairs, separated by the nasal septum. It is the first processing stage of the accessory olfactory system, after which chemical stimuli go to the accessory olfactory bulb, then to targets in the amygdala and hypothalamus. The vomeronasal organ is mainly used to detect pheromones, chemical messengers that carry information between individuals of the same species, hence is sometimes referred to as the 'sixth sense. ' The VNO has two separate types of neuronal receptors, V1R and V2R, which are seven-transmembrane receptors that are coupled to G proteins. The receptors are distinct from each other and form the large family of receptors in the main olfactory system. Evidence shows that the VNO responds to nonvolatile cues which stimulate the receptor neurons. Information is then transferred to the accessory olfactory bulb as well as other centres of the brain such as the anterior part of the hypothalamus. Its presence in many animals has been widely studied and the importance of the vomeronasal system to the role of reproduction and social behavior (through influence on anterior hypothalamus) has been shown in many studies. Its presence and functionality in humans is widely controversial, though most studies agree the organ regresses during fetal development. [WP,unvetted].

Seizures, which may progress to status epilepticus and neurologic sequelae, cranial nerve palsies, and photophobia may occur. EEE is associated with a high rate of morbidity and mortality.

Intra-bony cysts are most common in the jaws, because the mandible and maxilla are the only bones with epithelial components. That odontogenic epithelium is critical in normal tooth development. name: DT40
description: The DT40 chicken B cell line is derived from an avian leukosis virus (ALV)-induced bursal lymphoma. The ALV was injected intravenously into Hyline SC chickens and a resulting tumor was twice transplanted in vivo prior to cell culturing (Baba and Humphries, 1984; Baba et al., 1985). The DT40 cells are small, approximately 10 μm in diameter, and have a high nucleus to cytoplasm ratio (Fig. 1). They carry IgM on the surface, and although Baba et al. (1985) did not find evidence of secreted IgM, others have (Takagaki et al., 1996; Takami et al., 1999). DT40 cells do release ALV into the surroundings, but in negligible amounts (Baba et al., 1985). In keeping with the observation that nearly 85% of all ALV-induced tumors are disrupted in the c-myc locus, the DT40 cells have integrated the 3′ viral long terminal repeat (LTR) upstream of the c-myc gene ( Hayward et al., 1981). The 3′ LTR is in the same orientation as c-myc, elevating the transcription levels 100-fold in this cell line compared with normal avian bursal cells ( Baba et al., 1985). Whereas Baba et al. (1985) detected a normal and an altered c-myc allele, Kim et al. (1990) reported a possible mitotic recombination event among the parental alleles, as they describe the loss of the normal c-myc allele and instead find two copies of the altered c-myc gene. DT40 cells continue to undergo gene conversion, as seen by testing for the presence or absence of various restriction sites within the light chain variable region ( Thompson et al., 1987). Although the DT40 cell line may best be characterized as being a bursal B cell line, the ongoing gene conversion and the fact that v-myc transformed cells can reconstitute an ablated bursa of Fabricius suggests, that the DT40 cell line is arrested at a bursal stem cell stage of differentiation ( Baba et al., 1985; Thompson et al., 1987; McCormack et al., 1991).

The autosomal dominant trait is associated with abnormalities on the short arm of chromosome 16. Symptoms in patients with the autosomal dominant trait usually appear at middle age and include abdominal pain, hematuria, and high blood pressure. Patients may develop brain aneurysms and liver cysts. Patients with the autosomal recessive trait present with progressive renal failure early in life and symptoms resulting from hepatic fibrosis. The autosomal recessive trait is associated with abnormalities of chromosome 6. Polycystic kidney disease may also result as a side effect in patients on renal dialysis. [ NCI ]

description: An intraneural or extraneural neoplasm arising from nerve tissues and neural sheaths. It is composed of perineurial-like fibroblasts and Schwann cells. It usually presents as a localized cutaneous lesion and less often as a circumscribed peripheral nerve mass. Patients with neurofibromatosis type 1 present with multiple masses. Neurofibromas which arise from major nerves and plexiform neurofibromas are precursor lesions to malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumors.

name: neurofibroma

The tumors usually develop along peripheral or cranial nerves and are a central feature of NEUROFIBROMATOSIS 1, where they may occur intracranially or involve spinal roots. Pathologic features include fusiform enlargement of the involved nerve. Microscopic examination reveals a disorganized and loose cellular pattern with elongated nuclei intermixed with fibrous strands (MeSH).

name: Microcystic Renal Disease
description: A congenital renal disorder characterized by the presence of small cysts in the renal cortex and/or renal medulla. [ NCI ]

name: obsolete_spinal muscular atrophy
description: A group of disorders marked by progressive degeneration of motor neurons in the spinal cord resulting in weakness and muscular atrophy, usually without evidence of injury to the corticospinal tracts. Diseases in this category include Werdnig-Hoffmann disease and later onset SPINAL MUSCULAR ATROPHIES OF CHILDHOOD, most of which are hereditary. (Adams et al., Principles of Neurology, 6th ed, p1089)

name: skin fluorescence measurement

Skin fluorescence (SF) is a non-invasive marker of AGEs and is associated with the long-term complications of diabetes. SF increases with age and is also greater among individuals with diabetes

name: Malignant Ovarian Brenner Tumor
description: A malignant neoplasm that arises from the ovary and is characterized by the presence of an invasive malignant transitional cell component and nests of benign transitional cells in a fibrotic stroma. When the tumor is confined to the ovary, the prognosis is good.

name: Ossifying Fibromyxoid Tumor
description: A rare soft tissue tumor of uncertain lineage characterized by the presence of neoplastic spindle to round cells forming cords in a fibromyxoid stroma. The lesions are associated with the formation of metaplastic bone. Most patients present with painless subcutaneous masses. Recurrences have been reported in a minority of patients.

name: obsolete_vastus lateralis
description: The division of the quadriceps muscle that covers the outer anterior aspect of the femur, arises chiefly from the femur, and inserts into the outer border of the patella by a flat tendon which blends with that of the other divisions of the muscle and sends an expansion to the capsule of the knee.

name: HFF-Myc

name: Extraskeletal Ewing Sarcoma/Peripheral Primitive Neuroectodermal Tumor
description: A spectrum of malignant tumors arising from the soft tissues, characterized morphologically by the presence of small round cells. Ewing sarcoma and peripheral primitive neuroectodermal tumor represent the ends of a spectrum, with Ewing sarcoma lacking evidence of neural differentiation and the markers that characterize the peripheral primitive neuroectodermal tumor. Ewing sarcoma and peripheral primitive neuroectodermal tumor may share cytogenetic abnormalities, proto-oncogene expression, cell culture and immunohistochemical abnormalities. Pain and the presence of a mass are the most common clinical symptoms.

name: CATCH-seq
description: Capture of Associated Targets on CHromatin (CATCH)

name: Inclusion Body Fibromatosis
description: A rare benign neoplasm arising from the soft tissues of the digits, in young children. It is characterized by the presence of fibroblastic spindle cells, and intracytoplasmic eosinophilic spherical inclusions.

name: END-seq
description: DNA end resection and DSB discovery

name: cardiac troponin I measurement
description: Quantification of cardiac troponin I, typically measured in blood. Cardiac troponin I measurements are used as a marker of cardiac muscle damage and used in the diagnosis of myocardial infarction.

name: fat body mass
description: The weight of the individual's body fat.

name: x-linked ichthyosis with steryl-sulfatase deficiency
description: X-linked ichthyosis is clinically characterized by widespread, dark brown, polygonal scales and generalized dryness. Cutaneous manifestations are present soon after birth and usually do not improve with age. The histopathology of XLI typically shows compact hyperkeratosis and slight acanthosis with a normal granular layer (summary by Takeichi and Akiyama, 2016).
